                                                          
CCA on text data                                 Karl Stratos
                                      stratos@cs.columbia.edu
_____________________________________________________________
1. When you have a raw (but properly tokenized) text corpus 

(a) Count n-grams: 
python cca.py --corpus input/example/example.corpus

(b) Cutoff rare words in the n-grams (need unigram counts). 
Optionally, embed words you want to keep with --myvocab:
python cca.py --ngrams input/example/example.3grams --cutoff 1 --unigrams input/example/example.1grams [--myvocab input/pos/univ12.all]

(c) Extract features: 
python cca.py --ngrams input/example/example.3grams.cutoff1 --extract_views

(d) Run CCA on this feature file. Specify 
- m: number of CCA components
- kappa: pseudocounts for smoothing
python cca.py --views input/example/example.3grams.cutoff1.featurized --m 100 --kappa 5

_____________________________________________________________
2. When you have processed n-grams (e.g., Google n-grams), 
start from step (c).

